## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pdb/ipdbrawsymbol">IPDBRawSymbol</a> defines an interface used to represent an arbitrary symbol.

It exposes a monolithic interface consisting of accessors for the union of all properties that are valid for any symbol type. This interface is then wrapped by a concrete class which exposes only those set of methods valid for this particular symbol type. See <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/pdb/pdbsymbol-h">PDBSymbol.h</a> for more details.

Definition at line 45 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/pdb/ipdbrawsymbol-h">IPDBRawSymbol.h</a>.
